FBIS4-30667 "dreas125_m_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-125 Daily Report 14 May 1994 Thailand * Central Bank Chief, Others on Money-Laundering * Central Bank Chief, Others on Money-Laundering Banker Fears Impact of Law 94WD0404A Bangkok NAEO NA in Thai 14 May 94 p 7 94WD0404A Bangkok NAEO NA Thai CSO [Excerpt] Mr. Khanchit Kantangkun, the assistant managing director of the Krung Thai Bank, talked about the plan by officials to promulgate a money-laundering law in an effort to stop the laundering of "dirty" money. He said that if this law actually is promulgated, it will have a great effect on financial institutions, particularly commercial bank customers. Thus, officials should clearly stipulate the limitations of this law so that this does not affect depositors. [passage omitted]
